ormat_id": "2", "format": "2 - 640x1137"}, {"format_id": "dash-1203480901846164v", "ext": "mp4", "width": 720, "height": 1280, "tbr": 437.72, "format_note": "DASH video", "container": "mp4_dash", "vcodec": "avc1.64001f", "acodec": "none", "dynamic_range": "SDR", "url": "https://scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com/o1/v/t2/f2/m86/AQMgsmz7CL-9LMh3LlkE9hLItGwrGWVm19IjWgGdQKPN0lcrGwDkrM9gqiA8i0ayLIa_48QB6k7ZmbxG4rhyjwfUFuf_yHHMo8fgyfo.mp4?_nc_cat=108&_nc_sid=9ca052&_nc_ht=scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_ohc=OHDldOxPsHcQ7kNvwGXJuHT&%3D&ccb=17-1&_nc_gid=X7943jUzVlydD72ZakSr4Q&_nc_zt=28&_nc_ss=7a32e&oh=00_Af06XJYyExAmH4Pm1LeDeiiWPhgq5eixkhrwVN9UysjX6w&oe=69D38F59", "manifest_stream_number": 0, "is_dash_periods": true, "protocol": "https", "resolution": "720x1280", "aspect_ratio": 0.56, "filesize_approx": 303668, "http_headers": {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.106 Safari/537.36", "Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "video_ext": "mp4", "audio_ext": "none", "abr": 0, "vbr": 437.72, "format": "dash-1203480901846164v - 720x1280 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by cinesospeso", "description": "Osgood Perkins has officially cemented his status as the architect of modern atmospheric horror with Keeper (2025). Collaborating again with cinematographer Jeremy Cox, Perkins utilizes suffocating negative space and deliberate, voyeuristic framing to transform a simple cabin retreat into a claustrophobic nightmare. The terror here is purely architectural; the camera lingers on empty corners and open doorways, forcing the audience to actively scan the frame for threats that may not even exist.\nTatiana Maslany delivers a career-defining performance of unraveling sanity, grounding the folk-horror elements in a terrifyingly tangible emotional reality. While the screenplay by Nick Lepard builds a foundation of relationship toxicity, it is Perkins’ precise control over tone and sound design—specifically Edo Van Breemen’s subliminal score—that instills a physical sense of dread.This film proves that true horror lies not in the monster, but in the silence before it appears.\n\nFollow @cinesospeso for cinema analysis.\n.\n.\n\n#horrormovies #horrorfan #creepy", "duration": 5.55, "timestamp": 1765992455, "uploader_id": "78097213514", "uploader": "CineSospeso", "channel": "cinesospeso", "like_count": 33758, "comment_count": 481, "comments": [{"author": "joeydrizzdi_thekid", "author_id": "56414968922", "id": "18109660231832121", "text": "Overhated movie. Ts was incredible", "timestamp": 1774747722}, {"author": "empath00", "author_id": "14698509489", "id": "17992218425930358", "text": "So good", "timestamp": 1773741535}, {"author": "meowvinaasf", "author_id": "53473926431", "id": "18045916382734651", "text": "this was the dumbest movie of the year that basement scene was the only good part", "timestamp": 1773602851}, {"author": "rut_da_bahba", "author_id": "326609051", "id": "18352053748227043", "text": "You just gave away the only good 5 minutes of the movie. I've never seen so many plot holes. Terrible.", "timestamp": 1773579592}, {"author": "louwillfadeit", "author_id": "281878468", "id": "18129871582549283", "text": "Def not the creepiest it’s a cool story not a great movie though ok at best", "timestamp": 1773523532}, {"author": "jochan2104", "author_id": "222304920", "id": "18040680593751928", "text": "So damn boring movie, total dogshet", "timestamp": 1773372596}, {"author": "marius_krn_", "author_id": "1638536906", "id": "18307974406262633", "text": "Von wegen", "timestamp": 1773031080}], "thumbnails": [{"url": "https://scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/600161325_17851525512605515_978963651584505710_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_tt6&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6ImltYWdlX3VybGdlbi42MTB4MTA4NC5zZHIuZjgyNzg3LmRlZmF1bHRfY292ZXJ